To generate a Personal Access Token (PAT) on GitHub, follow these steps:

Log in to GitHub: Go to GitHub and log in to your account.
Navigate to Settings: Click on your profile picture in the top-right corner and select Settings.
Access Developer Settings: Scroll down and click on Developer settings in the left sidebar.
Generate a New Token: Click on Personal access tokens and then Generate new token.
Configure the Token:
Name: Give your token a descriptive name.
Expiration: Set an expiration date for the token.
Scopes: Select the scopes or permissions you want to grant this token. For example, if you want to use it for accessing repositories, select the repo scope.
Generate and Save: Click Generate token. Make sure to copy and save the token somewhere secure, as you wonâ€™t be able to see it again.
You can now use this token in place of your password for Git operations and API access123.

If you need any further assistance, feel free to ask!

